---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Nebular Reddening - ArXiv Atlas";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Nebular Reddening</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>Nebular reddening</strong> refers to the dust attenuation experienced by emission lines from H II regions. It is commonly estimated via the Balmer decrement (Hα/Hβ) and converted to E(B−V)_<sub>gas</sub> using an extinction curve (e.g., Cardelli et al. 1989) and Case B recombination assumptions (Karthikeyan et al. 2026, Section II.3.1). [Section II.3.1]
    </p>

    <h2 id="importance">Importance</h2>
    <p>Nebular reddening is crucial for correcting emission-line SFR indicators and for interpreting gas-phase metallicity diagnostics (Karthikeyan et al. 2026, Section II.3.2; Section III.3). [Section II.3.2; Section III.3]</p>

    <h2 id="see-also">See also</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/balmer_decrement" text="Balmer Decrement" /></li>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/gas_phase_metallicity" text="Gas-phase Metallicity" /></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Karthikeyan, S., Clarke, L., Shapley, A. E., et al. (2026). "Balmer Decrements and Nebular-Stellar Reddening in JADES Galaxies at 2.7&lt;z&lt;7." arXiv:2603.11338. <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11338">https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11338</a> (Section II.3.1).</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
